<br>
Correct me if I am wrong, but dont you just have to kill him before you kill the Spiroc Guardian, and he will respawn instantly?  If so, does anyone know the average number of times he needs to be killed for him to eventually drop the Ivory Sky Diamond?<br>
<br>
Also, how rare are the other pieces of the Girdle of Faith quest?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance. <p><img src= "http://home.mindspring.com/~dinobot69/_uimages/sig2.jpg" border=0></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubarrandaam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BarrandAam</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/13/01 12:00:16 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.health-tracker.com/pics/barr.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you farm the Spiroc Lord?</span><hr size=1> Kill him before guardian dies and he repops instantly<br>
<br>
SP killed him 7 times for the blades we needed and he had no diamond<br>
<br>
KoT said he dropped it on the 13th kill for them <p>-The Barr<BR>
<BR><b><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8248">Barraind Faylestar</a>
<BR></b>Knight of Marr, The <a target="new" href="http://www.spguild.com">Shining Path</a>'s researcher En-Garde and commonplace lootmonger<BR><i>"Fight for what was. Fight for what is. Fight for what will be. You are only dead when you stop fighting." </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubarrandaam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BarrandAam</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 3:43:39 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.health-tracker.com/pics/barr.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you farm the Spiroc Lord?</span><hr size=1> this probably doesnt need to be said but<br>
<br>
DONT KILL HIM AT HIS SPAWN POINT<br>
<br>
cause when he died, you will be insta dt'd and the fun of killing him starts sans 1-4 tanks(+1 for the initial sac of the lord) <p>-The Barr<BR>
<BR><b><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8248">Barraind Faylestar</a>
<BR></b>Knight of Marr, The <a target="new" href="http://www.spguild.com">Shining Path</a>'s researcher En-Garde and commonplace lootmonger<BR><i>"Fight for what was. Fight for what is. Fight for what will be. You are only dead when you stop fighting." </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustormwillow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormwillow</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://members.home.com/mheiberg/portraits/zeraicon01.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 9:48:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.socal.rr.com/innerloop/eqpics/ArezToV96.jpg width=96 height=107></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you farm the Spiroc Lord?</span><hr size=1> We attempted him last night with our guild.  There are 3 Vanquishers, each with 2 Spirocs.  You must kill the Vanquishers first before killing the other Spirocs else they repop instantly.  The Lord works the same way, repoping instantly if the Guardian is not dead.<br>
<br>
The Guardian is located on a far side of the island.  I'm not sure where the Lord is.  We tried some FD pulling to possibly cut down the number of mobs we had to fight, but it was futile.  We got all 3 Vanqs and thier guards everytime.  FD'ing is also very difficult because the Spirocs cast.  I was also DT'd 3 times by somehow aggroing the Spiroc Lord (I was playing the Monk).<br>
<br>
We only had 19 people up there, with 5 tanks.  I think a few more are required for this unless you can pull less than 9.  If anyone has some info on how to do this it would be great.<br>
<br>
I think my guild is close to the point of abandoning the warrior epic along with the SK and Pally Haste belt.  Seems the diamond is super rare anyway and there are better weapons than the warrior epic so I guess its not that big a deal.<br>
<br>
Time to sell the RBG and find a RBB.  Actually I think camping the haste belt in Sirens may be a good alternative.<br>
<br>
Arez 59 Paladin<br>
Zera 57 Druid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueqjonze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqjonze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 9:52:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you farm the Spiroc Lord?</span><hr size=1> I'd want to make him respawn over and over and over untill I got my thingie too, but isn't that kind of an exploit? <p><b>Jonze</b> 51 Paladin
<br><a href="http://www.eqwhitewind.com"> White Wind on Drinal</a>
<a href=" http://photos.yahoo.com/eqjonze/"> My Photo Album </a>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushaorinorsoulbringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaorinor Soulbringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 11:06:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you farm the Spiroc Lord?</span><hr size=1> Mobs respawn...this just makes it faster...he's a guaranteed spawn anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukoronastoutheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korona Stoutheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 11:23:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you farm the Spiroc Lord?</span><hr size=1> Once you have the island down to the Lord and the Guardian, the trick is to kill the lord in such a place that -- when Sirran spawns -- you can kill the next lord without aggro'ing Sirran.<br>
<br>
So, accordingly, you never kill a lord at his spawn point unless you have already popped Sirran and Sirran is at the other side of the island.  When Sirran despawns, you yank the lord again to the other side of the island, kill him there, Sirran pops again, and then you can kill the lord at his spawn point (again until Sirran despawns).<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udagnyblazestorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dagny Blazestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 4:15:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you farm the Spiroc Lord?</span><hr size=1> Exactly. If you kill him at his spawn point and Sirran isn't up, you just wiped out. Spiroc lord dies, Sirran pops, new spiroc lord pops and aggros on you. Sirran assists it......it goes downhill from there. <p><p><center><img src="http://members.home.net/dtlee1974/dagnysig.gif"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/14/01 4:52:14 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/skfitz/valhood.jpg height=124 width=124></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do you farm the Spiroc Lord?</span><hr size=1> 1. Nothing in Plane of Air is an exploit IMO, none of the usual rules seem to apply up there :pp<br>
<br>
2. Breaking the island is quite difficult. We went up to farm the Lord for a while a few months back, actually about a week after they put the ivory sky diamond in, and we had to break the island 2x due to camping out there late on Saturday then returning early Sunday. There is a very small safe point where you can hang out and not get agroed, but unfortunately I can't really tell you where it is very well, its right along the edge of the island.  We managed to break the first time in one LOONG tough fight when just about everyone died except a camped cleric, but we managed to get all the vanquishers so we were good.  We managed to break the second time w/o any high level enchanters, hehe, that was kind of fun. But rather painful--<br>
<br>
3. We got 2 ivory sky diamonds out of probably 30 lords (we got blades for all our warriors who were high enough lvl  to attend).  Both I and the other paladin on the raid had gotten the Diaphanous Globe on the way up, and neither of us had gotten the Silvery Girdle.   He was able to buy a girdle in North Freeport (mith marr's auction zone) and complete his quest.   A friend of mine had not 1 but 2 (!) in the bank, and generously gave me one, so I now have the Girdle of Faith. :)  Actually I just finished it last week -- in time for Luclin, hehe, I may have to come out of retirement. <br>
<br>
